<!-- BacSeq2 AMR/VFDB/plasmid/MGE/prophage report section -->
<section id="amr-mge" class="section-card">
  <h2>AMR, virulence, plasmid, mobile element, and prophage screening</h2>
  <p class="report-note">
    BacSeq2 compares multiple genomic AMR resources and reports genomic determinants only.
    These results should not be interpreted as a clinical antibiogram unless AST phenotype data are provided.
  </p>

  <div class="summary-grid">
    <div class="metric-card">
      <span class="metric-label">AMRFinderPlus hits</span>
      <span class="metric-value">{{ amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_hits | default('NA') }}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
      <span class="metric-label">CARD/RGI hits</span>
      <span class="metric-value">{{ amr_mge.amr.card_rgi_hits | default('NA') }}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="metric-card">
      <span class="metric-label">VFDB hits</span>
      <span class="metric-value">{{ amr_mge.virulence.vfdb_hits | default('NA') }}</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>AMR comparison</h3>
  <p>
    AMRFinderPlus, CARD/RGI, and ResFinder results are intentionally shown side-by-side because each database has
    different curation scope and detection logic. Consensus hits across multiple tools should be prioritized, while
    tool-specific hits should be reviewed manually.
  </p>

  <h3>Genetic context</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>MOB-suite:</strong> plasmid reconstruction and plasmid-like contig evidence.</li>
    <li><strong>PlasmidFinder:</strong> plasmid replicon screening.</li>
    <li><strong>MobileElementFinder/MEFinder, IntegronFinder, and ISEScan:</strong> mobile element context.</li>
    <li><strong>Phigaro/geNomad:</strong> prophage and virus/provirus screening.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Preview: AMRFinderPlus</h3>
  <div class="table-responsive">
    <table class="display compact">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          {% if amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_preview and amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_preview[0] %}
            {% for key in amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_preview[0].keys() %}<th>{{ key }}</th>{% endfor %}
          {% else %}
            <th>Status</th>
          {% endif %}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% if amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_preview %}
          {% for row in amr_mge.amr.amrfinderplus_preview %}
            <tr>{% for value in row.values() %}<td>{{ value }}</td>{% endfor %}</tr>
          {% endfor %}
        {% else %}
          <tr><td>No AMRFinderPlus hits or file unavailable.</td></tr>
        {% endif %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>
